author: Thomas Hanssen Nornes
commit_message:
Limit event triggering to current subscribers

If you needed to register more subscribers to  an event inside the
execution context of that same event you would run into recursion
problems. The solution is to create a copy of the current
subscribers before executing them.

author: ajpen
commit_message:
Support defining event names in constructor.

This commit implements the enhancement requested in #1.

Events that are initialized by a list/tuple of event names,
will have those names stored in __events__, local to that instance only.

Both __events__ and __class__.__events__ will be evaluated, long as they
exist. They can but should not be used together.

author: ajpen
commit_message:
Add support for simultaneous use of both methods

This commit allows Events objects to be defined using both the
__events__ class attribute and the instance method. Using both
methods allow instances to be restricted to a subset of the
events defined in __events__.

author: Øyvind Heddeland Instefjord
commit_message:
Fix Events.__len__ counting __events__

If __events__ is set in __init__ it
will be part of __dict__, making
the output of __len__ wrong.
Fix is to return the length of
__iter__ which only outputs
the attributes of interest
(_EventSlot attributes)
